The paper discusses the use of network coding to improve the reliability and efficiency of millimeter-wave communication systems, which are typically used in wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses information theory concepts such as path-loss and channel switching, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely category. The use of millimeter-wave bands for communication is a key aspect of the paper, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the limitations of millimeter-wave communication, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.COM (Computers and Society).
